{"title": "Unsanitized user input in format string", "summary": "  If an application includes user input directly in a format string, an attacker can use format specifiers in the user input to produce misleading or fabricated messages. ", "description": "\n\nIf an application includes user input directly in a format string, an\nattacker can use format specifiers in the user input to produce misleading\nor fabricated messages.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid format strings containing user input:\n\n```php\nsprintf(\"The value was ${_GET[\"value\"]}\");\n```\n\n\u2705 Use a literal format string with additional arguments:\n\n```php\nsprintf(\"The value was %s\", $_GET[\"value\"]);\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-134"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_format_string_using_user_input"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}